<TITLE> Contempt petition filed against minister Faruque Khan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 28 (bdnews24.com)  A contempt of court petition has been filed against commerce minister Faruque Khan. Rights group Human Rights and Peace for Bangladesh filed the petition with the bench of justices Syed Mahmud Hossain and ATM Fazle Kabir on Sunday against Khan for taking measures to stop removal of jetties of City Group in the river Shitalakhya ind efiance of a High Court order. The court is likely to hold a hearing Tuesday, HRPB lawyer Manzil Morshed said. The High Court in June last year ordered authorities to take measures against encroachment by illegal structures from the rivers around the capital. Narayanganj additional deputy commissioner earlier this month asked City Group of Industries to remove illegal structures, including three jetties, from the river bank located at Rupshi village under Rupganj upazila following the High Court order. The commerce minister on Feb 22 sent a letter to the shipping ministry asking it to take measures to prevent dismantling of the jetties, the petitioner said. The City Group also filed a petition challenging the High Court order but it was dismissed on Feb 23. bdn
